File: Maria Ramos. JOHANNESBURG - Maria Ramos has been appointed AngloGold Ashanti board chairperson. She replaces ANC stalwart and businessman Sipho Pityana. Ramos chaired the Absa board for a decade before retiring in February last year. READ: Absa CEO Maria Ramos to retire She is been a director at AngloGold Ashanti since May last year. The mining giant says Pityana chaired the board over a time when AngloGold Ashanti followed a clear strategy of capital discipline and improved sustainability.